LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
HOUSE BILL NO. 88
BY JUDICIARY, RULES AND ADMINISTRATION COMMITTEE
1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO COMMERCIAL SEXUAL ACTIVITY; AMENDING SECTION 18-5614, IDAHO
3 CODE, TO PROVIDE THAT SOLICITING COMMERCIAL SEXUAL ACTIVITY SHALL BE A
4 FELONY AND TO MAKE A TECHNICAL CORRECTION; AND DECLARING AN EMERGENCY
5 AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.
6 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
7 SECTION 1. That Section 18-5614, Idaho Code, be, and the same is hereby
8 amended to read as follows:
9 18-5614. SOLICITING COMMERCIAL SEXUAL ACTIVITY. (1) A person is
10 guilty of soliciting commercial sexual activity when he or she:
11 (a) Pays, offers to pay, or agrees to pay another person a fee for the
12 purpose of engaging in sexual contact; or
13 (b) Offers a third person to engage in, or agrees to provide a third per-
14 son to engage in, sexual contact in return for a fee.
15 (2) Soliciting commercial sexual activity shall be a misdemeanor, pro-
16 vided that a second or subsequent conviction therefor shall be a felony. Any
17 person convicted of a misdemeanor violation of this section shall be sen-
18 tenced to a minimum period of confinement of five (5) days in jail and may
19 be sentenced to up to one (1) year in jail or fined up to two thousand dol-
20 lars ($2,000), or both. The minimum period of confinement shall be served in
21 a county jail, and a court shall not have the power to suspend, withhold, re-
22 tain jurisdiction over, or commute the minimum period of confinement imposed
23 pursuant to this section felony.
24 SECTION 2. An emergency existing therefor, which emergency is hereby
25 declared to exist, this act shall be in full force and effect on and after
26 July 1, 2025.

